WEBVTT

00:04.136 --> 00:06.240
[ Man ] One, two! One, two, three!

00:34.000 --> 00:35.585
- Guidance system?
- On-line.

00:35.655 --> 00:37.067
- Autopilot?
- Present.

00:37.137 --> 00:39.551
- Dark matter indicator?
- Making a noise.

00:39.619 --> 00:42.240
All systems operational.
Let's rock.

00:51.274 --> 00:55.000
[ Horns Honking,
People Shouting ]

00:57.067 --> 01:00.551
Gentlemen, I've completed
my report on the crash.

01:00.619 --> 01:03.896
Whoa! I'm not readin' that crap!
Summarize it in one word.

01:03.965 --> 01:06.412
- Sabotage.
- [ All Gasp ]

01:06.481 --> 01:08.412
This is a normal L-unit.
Without it,

01:08.481 --> 01:11.343
space travel is but
the fevered dream of a madman.

01:11.412 --> 01:12.688
Of course!Duh!

01:12.757 --> 01:15.793
- It's an important unit.
- And this, my friends,

01:15.861 --> 01:18.343
is the L-unit I just
removed from the ship.

01:18.412 --> 01:20.655
[ All Gasp ]

01:20.724 --> 01:23.481
That doesn't look like an "L"
at all, unless you count
lowercase.

01:23.551 --> 01:25.481
You know we don't!Ooh!

01:25.551 --> 01:30.481
Whoever did this was strong.
This is 340 pounds
of Tonka-tough steel.

01:30.551 --> 01:32.965
Hmm. It should
look like this.

01:33.033 --> 01:35.585
But instead
it looks like this.

01:35.655 --> 01:39.481
-Who would do a thing like that?
-Who coulddo a thing like that?

01:39.551 --> 01:42.551
And by "that" I mean this.

01:42.620 --> 01:46.206
Well, gang, it looks like
we have another mystery
on our hands.

01:46.275 --> 01:48.758
I'd better make a chart
of the suspects.

01:48.826 --> 01:51.965
I'll begin by drawing
a line with my straightedge.

01:52.033 --> 01:55.137
[ Gasps ]
Sweet lamprey of Santa Fe!

01:55.206 --> 01:57.688
My edge has been bent!

01:57.758 --> 02:01.551
My javelin too!
It's ruined!

02:01.620 --> 02:04.310
Now we'll never beat
Jupiter State.

02:04.379 --> 02:08.931
My Slinky! My cuddly
little pet Slinky!

02:09.000 --> 02:11.516
[ Sobbing ]

02:11.586 --> 02:14.550
What's all the hubbub?

02:14.620 --> 02:16.965
My God! Even
the professor's been bent!

02:17.033 --> 02:21.068
Thank you for your sympathy,
talking square of linoleum.

02:21.137 --> 02:23.033
I'll get you fixed up.

02:23.103 --> 02:25.068
Ohhh!That's fine.

02:25.137 --> 02:28.896
Wait a minute! Bender,
what did you just do
to the professor?

02:28.965 --> 02:31.516
- I bent him.
- [ All Gasp ]

02:31.586 --> 02:33.516
Bender! J'accuse.

02:33.586 --> 02:35.826
Oh, I see.
A bunch of stuff gets bent,

02:35.896 --> 02:38.103
so it must be the robot
designed for bending.

02:38.171 --> 02:40.137
I know how to settle this.

02:40.206 --> 02:42.826
We'll check last night's
surveillance tapes.Surveillance?

02:42.896 --> 02:45.033
What tapes?You've seen me naked?

02:45.103 --> 02:48.137
♪♪ [ Humming ]

02:48.206 --> 02:51.723
Ah! Last night's tape.
It was right next to
"Bathroom Bloopers Four."

02:55.171 --> 02:58.896
[ Snoring ][ Owls Hooting ]

02:58.965 --> 03:02.793
[ Bender ] See? Nothin'. Told you, losers!

03:02.861 --> 03:05.516
Wait. There on the screen. It's that guy you are!

03:05.586 --> 03:07.516
[ All Gasp ]I'm sleepwalkin'.

03:07.586 --> 03:10.481
Dear Lord, we've got
robots on the ceiling!

03:10.550 --> 03:14.586
[ Babbling ]

03:17.137 --> 03:20.620
[ Grunting ]

03:20.688 --> 03:22.965
[ All Gasping ]

03:30.688 --> 03:32.826
[ Bones Cracking ][ Groans ]

03:32.896 --> 03:35.516
[ Snoring Continues ]

03:35.586 --> 03:38.206
You weren't sleepwalking.
You were sleep-bending.

03:38.275 --> 03:42.655
This is quite a shock!
On the other hand, it's not
surprising in the least.

03:42.723 --> 03:47.655
After all, I've been bending
since the day I was built.

03:47.723 --> 03:53.033
[ Bender Narrating ] I was born on an assembly line in the bad part of Tijuana.

03:53.103 --> 03:55.861
[ Squeaking ]

03:55.930 --> 04:00.205
Mama. Wah! Wah! Wah!

04:00.275 --> 04:02.448
[ Moaning ]

04:02.516 --> 04:04.620
[ Gulping ]

04:07.240 --> 04:09.275
[ Beeping ]

04:18.516 --> 04:20.723
Hooray!
I graduated!

04:20.793 --> 04:23.310
Time to bend around Europe
for a few months,

04:23.379 --> 04:25.447
then get a job bending.

04:25.516 --> 04:29.413
You remember your own birth?Sure. It was only
four years ago.

04:29.481 --> 04:33.481
- You're only four years old?
- Precocious little scamp,
ain't I?

04:35.689 --> 04:38.481
Hmm. Bender must have
a pent-up need to bend...

04:38.550 --> 04:42.000
that's not being satisfied
by his bend-free lifestyle.

04:42.067 --> 04:46.240
Then he can't stay here.
He's a menace to every straight
person in the company.

04:46.310 --> 04:49.757
Go satisfy your bend lust,

04:49.826 --> 04:52.862
and don't you come back
to work until you do!

04:52.930 --> 04:56.310
[ Chanting ]
No more bending! No more work!

04:56.379 --> 04:58.896
Give us a raise,
you big fat jerk!

04:58.965 --> 05:00.964
Nevers!

05:01.033 --> 05:05.310
[ Whistles ]
Yo! The mafia supports ya!

05:05.379 --> 05:08.310
But don't tell no one.
Spread the word.

05:08.379 --> 05:11.343
As the duly elected mobsters
of this union,

05:11.413 --> 05:15.137
it's our duty to support
the struggle of these
proud, lazy slobs.

05:15.206 --> 05:17.930
Yeah, but what if management
remains "intragnizent"?

05:18.000 --> 05:20.862
From the context,
it is clear what you mean.

05:20.930 --> 05:23.896
In that case, Clamps may have
a little surprise for them.

05:23.964 --> 05:26.930
The clamps! Right?

05:27.000 --> 05:30.343
[ Sinister Laughing ]

05:30.413 --> 05:33.862
[ Low Chanting ]Ah, no! A strike?

05:33.930 --> 05:36.413
Now I'll never
get to bend anything!

05:36.481 --> 05:39.379
Oh, woe is Bender!Hang tough, brother.

05:39.447 --> 05:42.896
Management refused our demand
to switch casual Friday
to Monday.

05:42.965 --> 05:46.930
What?And now they're hiring scabs
at 10 times the normal wage.

05:47.000 --> 05:51.896
Ten times normal wage!
I'll give those jerks what for!

05:51.965 --> 05:56.240
[ Angry Chattering ]

05:56.310 --> 05:59.000
Welcomes aboard, scab.Great to be here.

05:59.067 --> 06:04.723
Come on. I'll introduces you
to your scab coworkers
you'll be scabbin' with.

06:04.793 --> 06:08.343
This here's
our scab foreman.

06:08.413 --> 06:10.033
- Flexo?
- Bender?

06:10.103 --> 06:13.689
Hey, sorry you got sent
to that South American
Turkish prison...

06:13.757 --> 06:16.689
instead of me on account
of mistaken identity.

06:16.757 --> 06:21.206
You bastard!
They treated me like an animal!
And that's what I became!

06:21.274 --> 06:25.757
[ Laughs ]
Nah, you're all right.
Good to see ya, buddy.

06:25.826 --> 06:28.723
And here's another scab
what also works here.

06:28.793 --> 06:32.000
- Angleene.
- [ Gasps ]

06:34.137 --> 06:35.481
Hello!

06:36.896 --> 06:39.689
Hey! Youse guyses wanna move that thing?

06:45.103 --> 06:49.965
- Hello!
- [ Deep Laughter, Coughs ]

06:52.067 --> 06:54.481
[ Chanting ]
Give us a raise,
you big fat jerk!

06:54.550 --> 06:57.413
[ Foreman ] Nevers![ Grunting ]

06:57.481 --> 07:00.826
[ Grunting Continues ]

07:07.103 --> 07:09.793
[ Sighs ]
Ow!

07:12.447 --> 07:16.379
Um, hi, Angleene.
Whatcha up to?

07:16.447 --> 07:20.103
Makin' hangers.
Guidance counselor said
I had a knack for it.

07:20.172 --> 07:23.964
That's cool. That's cool.
So, um, uh,

07:24.033 --> 07:27.067
I was wonderin' if--
you know, it's cool if not--

07:27.137 --> 07:29.516
but what are you doin'
after work?

07:29.586 --> 07:32.137
What I always do.
Jack squat.

07:32.206 --> 07:36.343
[ Chuckles ]
Me too. Man, we have
a lot in common, huh?

07:36.413 --> 07:39.757
Well, we are made of
virtually identical components.

07:39.826 --> 07:44.274
Are you sure?
Maybe I should sneak a peak
at your access panel.

07:44.343 --> 07:46.793
Hey, according
to the Scab Handbook,

07:46.862 --> 07:49.723
that's extremely
inappropriate banter.

07:49.793 --> 07:53.379
And that's just
the way I like it.

07:56.793 --> 07:59.172
Haile H. Selassie!

07:59.240 --> 08:02.550
There, little friend.
Good as new.

08:04.206 --> 08:07.310
[ Sobbing ]

08:07.379 --> 08:10.862
[ Farnsworth ]
What an exquisite day![ Wheels Squeaking ]

08:10.930 --> 08:15.033
That azure sky.
The verdant treetops.

08:15.103 --> 08:20.689
Those delightful birds
with their chirp, chirp, chirp
and their tweet, tweet, splat.

08:20.757 --> 08:23.000
Professor, I've never
seen you so cheerful.

08:23.067 --> 08:26.310
What the hell's
wrong with you?Hmm. I'm not quite sure.

08:26.379 --> 08:30.964
Perhaps seeing things
from a new perspective has
reminded me of life's beauty.

08:31.033 --> 08:35.895
Or perhaps my new posture
is causing blood to pool
in the back of my brain,

08:35.965 --> 08:38.793
resulting in a mild
delirium.

08:38.861 --> 08:41.931
Incidentally, you have
a dime up your nose.

08:42.000 --> 08:44.136
I wish.
It's a nickel.

08:44.206 --> 08:47.102
[ Murmuring ]Union forever!

08:47.172 --> 08:50.309
Lousy scabs! They can't
do those things! Et cetera!

08:52.240 --> 08:54.586
[ Grunting ]

08:54.654 --> 08:58.586
I bet watchin' me bend
girders like this turns
your legs all rubbery.

08:58.654 --> 09:00.793
Well, my legs aremade of rubber.

09:00.861 --> 09:04.551
And anyway, I am just
as strong as you are, Mac.

09:04.620 --> 09:06.965
Oh, yeah? Prove it.

09:07.033 --> 09:09.931
[ Grunting ]

09:12.895 --> 09:15.000
[ Groans ]

09:15.067 --> 09:17.136
Here, let me help you.

09:38.067 --> 09:41.240
[ Electricity Crackling ]

